Hello all,
I am looking for camera lenses for an M12 arducam for both April tags and object detection. The recommended FOV is 100 degrees for AT and 180 degrees for OD. What I am struggling with is a 100-degree lens with low distortion. It would be preferable if it were on Amazon, but it is not required.
Thank you

I bought a replacement for our OV9281 USB Camera on the advice of the Arducam discord.

uctronics.com

Arducam 1/2.7

Features: Arducam Lens M27280M07S featuring low distortion Module number:M27280M07S Optical Format: 1/2.7” Distortion: 1.5% Effective Focal Length: 2.8mm 35mm equivalent focal length: 30.27mm FOV on 1/2.7”sensor(D/H/V):103°/95°/63° FOV on...

Price: USD 12.99

edit: Also was suggested, “You’d better add a comment when placing order as the lens above has IR cut filter while it should be sensitive to infrared light (NoIR) on this mono sensor.”
